<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870626-0067 </DOCNO><HL> Allied-Signal's UnitGets $384 Million JobFor Shuttle Services</HL><DD> 06/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ALD GOVMTAEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The National Aeronautics and Space Administration awarded a $384 million contract to Bendix Field Engineering Corp. for communications and engineering services.    The company, a unit of Allied-Signal Inc. in Morristown, N.J., will be under contract to the Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Md. The center is responsible for communications between the ground and the shuttle crew during space flights and for tracking the shuttle.    Taking effect in November, the contract will extend for two years and 10 1/2 months, with an additional two-year period as an option. The $384 million estimated cost covers the entire period.    The contract will provide for 2,000 people at facilities in Greenbelt; Merritt Island Ground Station near Cape Canaveral, Fla.; White Sands Ground Terminal near White Sands, N.M.; Bermuda Tracking Station, and at Bendix facilities in Columbia, Md. </TEXT></DOC>